    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "(Part of https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/39006, https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/22313 read those before commenting here.)\n\n## Problem\n\nUnconvential UI for enabling/disabling treesitter support for highlighting, folding, etc.\n\n## Proposal\n\n- Add `syntax=legacy`; make `syntax=treesitter` the default (if highlight queries are available)\n    - `syntax=ON` falls back to legacy if missing treesitter parser/queries.\n- Add `foldmethod=treesitter` option, fallback to `foldmethod=syntax` if missing treesitter parser/queries.\n- `indentexpr=''` defaults to treesitter indenting. (If legacy `cindent` is really needed, we can provide a snowflake option for it.)\n    - Alternative: introduce `indentexpr=treesitter`\n- Deprecate `vim.treesitter.start()`/`stop()`, in favor of `syntax=treesitter` / `foldmethod=treesitter`.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- `vim.treesitter.enable()` is out of scope. Leverage the vim options system.\n- `vim.treesitter.config()` is out of scope. Leverage the vim options system.\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
